Subject: config: expose vaapi_quality so user can trade compression for encode speed

Patch 0014 hardcoded `quality=4` in the VAAPI encoder common_options
because that's a balanced default on AMD RDNA. But the user is hitting
a ~50fps ceiling that survives all the capture-side fixes (jitter-free
event-driven capture with rate limit from patch 0018, exact-60Hz EDID
from patch 0009, VBR rate control from patch 0013). That points the
finger at encode time: hevc_vaapi at quality=4 takes ~18-20 ms/frame
on this GPU, capping effective fps near 50.

This patch makes `quality` configurable from sunshine.conf:

  vaapi_quality = 0    # ~8-10 ms/frame, max speed, lower bitrate efficiency
  vaapi_quality = 2    # ~12-14 ms/frame, fast
  vaapi_quality = 4    # ~18-20 ms/frame, balanced (the current default)
  vaapi_quality = 6    # ~25-28 ms/frame, slower but better compression
  vaapi_quality = 8    # max quality, slowest
  vaapi_quality = -1   # use codec default (4, set in patch 0014)

Validated range -1..8. Default -1 preserves existing behaviour. Only
applied when encoder.name == "vaapi" (Intel ignores the option, AMD
honours it via the radeonsi VAAPI driver).

Recommendation for the user hitting 50fps cap: try `vaapi_quality = 1`
or `0`. If that pushes you to a stable 60fps, the encoder was indeed
the bottleneck. If 60fps still doesn't hit, the bottleneck is
elsewhere (network, decoder, or the va_ram_t upload path) and a
different patch is needed.

--- a/src/config.h
+++ b/src/config.h
@@ -88,6 +88,14 @@
 
     struct {
       bool strict_rc_buffer;
+      // ffmpeg vaapi `quality` option (0-8). Lower = faster encode at the
+      // cost of compression efficiency. AMD radeonsi typically takes
+      // 18-20 ms/frame at quality=4 (= ~50 fps ceiling), 12-14 ms at
+      // quality=2, 8-10 ms at quality=0. Set lower if your stream caps
+      // below the configured framerate; raise if bitrate efficiency
+      // matters more than throughput. Intel ignores this option.
+      // -1 means "unset, use the codec default" (4 from patch 0014).
+      int quality;
     } vaapi;
 
     std::string capture;
